args: Whew! That takes care of that! 'Bout time,\ntoo—I'm so hungry, I could eat a ham\nthe size of a house.
We've been fighting more or less nonstop\nsince morning, so let's get ourselves\nsomething to ea—
Oy, look at THIS hot little number!\nHow ya doin', buttercup?
Huh. Not every day you see lowlifes\nsauntering about in broad daylight.
Hey! Girlie! I know ya can hear me\nwhat with them giant ears!
Blimey, that's it! Nobody gives me the\nsilent treatment and gets away with it!
He's about to fight that woman!\nLuca! Ranzal! With me!
Holy mother of cats... Didja SEE that?\nShe dodged him when he was right\nin her face!
Grr... I dunno how ya did that,\nbut it ain't gonna happen again!
Gahar har! Can't ignore me now, can ya?!\nNext time maybe you'll remember yer\ndamn manners!

What's this then? Ya really wanna scrap
with ME? Gahaaaar har har! Them little
stick arms don't stand a chance! But hey,
I never turn down a fight. C'mon, girlie!
Uh, guys? Correct me if I'm wrong,\nbut she's got her blade at that guy's throat.
Looks like he picked the wrong lady\nto rumble with.
I am no lady. My name is Odetta.
I am me, and that is enough.
Holy guacamole! She sent him packing!
You've quite the sword arm on you, miss!\nEr, or rather...Odetta, was it?
That boorish thug has been giving us\nno end of trouble. Thank you for ridding\nus of his foul presence!
We haven't much to offer in way of thanks,\nbut feel free to order whatever food you \nlike, on the house!
A most generous offer, thank you.\nNow then... Hmm...
Wh-what the? She's comin' right for us!\nAlert! Alert! Dive, dive, dive!
Pardon me, but if this seat isn't taken,\nmight I burden you with my company?
It would be our pleasure.\nPlease, have a seat.
How do you know his name?
Oh, a little birdie told me. One learns all\nmanner of interesting things on the road.
I am indeed. My name is Odetta,\nand I travel so that I might one day\nfind myself in entirely new worlds!
You're gonna need to run that by me again.\n...Er, slowly, if possible.
I seek what is unknown—and the unknown\nis what is unknown to me! That is of which\nI speak when I speak of entirely new wor—
I do not need you to understand.\nAll I require at this time is your consent.
Okay, I definitely want you to run\nTHAT one by me again.
I wish to be taken to your castle.\nMight I ask this of you?
Are you kidding me?! Hold up. Time out.\n{player_name}, get over here!
Did you not find it at ALL weird that we're\nfailing to communicate with this woman\neven though we speak the same language?
I got no clue what the hey she's on about,\nespecially with all that ＂new world＂ jazz!
Notte's right. Hell, she might be a member\nof some nutty sect—AND she's good with a\nsword! You follow? She's dangerous!
Er, so? I mean, we already have a number\nof outstanding—yet slightly odd—warriors\nback at the Halidom.
I'm sure you'll understand her better\nonce you get to know her.
Has your small council reached consensus,\n{player_name}?
Will you take me to your castle?
You're more than welcome, Odetta—\nbut in exchange, I'd like to hear some\ntales from your travels.
Better buckle up, folks. Ain't no goin' back\nonce his soft side kicks in.
Par for the course, is it not?
Yet while this woman is still a stranger,\nso long as we give our all to protecting\nHis Highness, everything should be well.
Goodness gracious! There are so many\nthings I have never seen before...\nHow utterly magnificent!
That's hardly surprising,\ngiven the age of this castle.
Oh my—this painting! I've never seen such\na style. How terribly fascinating...
Actually, erm...I painted that.\nB-but what is it doing here?!
Regardless, please stop staring at it.\nIt is certainly not the kind of thing that\nwarrants such prolonged appreciation.
That is where you're wrong. This is\nentirely new to me, which means it\npossesses tremendous value.
Break out the axe and call me stumped,\n'cause I got no clue what to make of her.
She may seem confusing to us at the\nmoment, but in time—
Pardon me, but I must ask permission to\nremain here for the time being. Would\nthat be all right, {player_name}?

This castle is simply enormous, you see,
and it will take time to see it all. There is
a whole new world waiting for me here,
and I must see every nook and cranny!
You can stay as long as you like.
I offer you my most profound gratitude.
I dunno, boss. Ya sure about this?
The only reason we find her confusing is\nbecause we know so little about her.
Much like how she has yet to know every\nnook and cranny of the Halidom.
So yer sayin' she's like an entirely\nnew world to us or...somethin'?
Exactly. Now let's all head over and\ngive her a warm Halidom welcome.
Yeesh. I sure hope yer right about this...
